Hi, it me, you know, Andres, but just call me Tuti, that gonna be easier for both. Now just let me introduce myself, I am 22 years old and I am studying at UTN in San Francisco, Córdoba, Argentina.
I am in the last steps before graduate, I am interested in videogames, movies, photography and music (specially post-punk).

Well, I worked on a project doing the Login and making the backend with ASPNET, and I used the EntityFramework with an SQL database.
Also I Know JavaScript, If you take a look in my GitHub repos, you can see in DSTP1 (Sorry for that strange name, this is the abbreviation of subject and project), I used APIs and also I know how to use the DOM.
My objetives in a short term is work for get some expirience and learn new technologies (mainly FrontEnd but I am also open to learn BackEnd).

Children.p: think the most important of that kind of CV or portfolio is talk about my skills, if you are a recruiter I think is kinda obvious I know HTML, CSS and Tailwind, but there are some projects on C# and dotnet where I used it as an API and also using and MVC architecture with ASPNET.
